{
  "id": "019d33e3-3a8b-7432-8f20-c186a3400070",
  "content": "# Spoke Design Review Fixes (2026-03-28)\n\nAll 8 Critical, 13 Important, 14 Low, and 10 Minor issues from the 5-persona review have been addressed.\n\n## Key Security Fixes\n- MCP bearer token auth for write operations (generated at startup, injected into spokes)\n- Per-spoke cryptographic agent tokens (agent_id + bcrypt hash, validated on writes)\n- Non-root spoke containers (USER spoke in Dockerfile)\n- Scoped GITHUB_TOKEN (fine-grained PAT, documented minimum permissions)\n- Pinned Claude Code version (never @latest at runtime)\n- Restricted Bash permissions (allow-list of git/cargo/npm/gh, deny docker/ssh)\n\n## Key Reliability Fixes\n- HubContext returns Result, never panics\n- Duplicate spoke name guard with --force flag\n- Network selection: filter system networks, prefer devcontainer, require config if ambiguous\n- Container detection check (/.dockerenv or /proc/1/cgroup)\n- Pre-flight validation (Docker, credentials, GITHUB_TOKEN, disk space)\n- Startup health gate (wait for hub MCP before starting Claude Code)\n- Trap-based error reporting to corvia on entrypoint failure\n- Default resource limits (4GB memory, 512 cpu_shares, log rotation)\n- Destroy --all requires confirmation\n- Git clone retry with 3 attempts\n\n## Key UX Fixes\n- spoke list shows failure reason column\n- Branch naming from issue title via gh API\n- Default branch queried dynamically (not hardcoded master)\n- spoke restart command (preserves repo checkout)\n- spoke check command (validates environment)\n\nDoc: docs/decisions/2026-03-28-spoke-design-review-fixes.md",
  "source_version": "mcp",
  "scope_id": "corvia",
